If you want to add texture
- Go to Game1.cs
- Write ->  Texture2D texture; // texture is a variable name
- Write in LoadContent() -> texture= Content.Load<Texture2D>("name"); // name is the name of your png file 
- Write in Draw() -> _spriteBatch.Begin() // If the texture was blurry, write this in parantheses (for pixel art) -> samplerState: samplerState.PointClamp
                     _spriteBatch.Draw(texture, new Vector2(100,100), Color.White)  //Vector2(x,y)
                                             or
                     _spriteBatch.Draw(texture, new Rectangle (100,100,100,100), Color.White)  //Rectangle(x,y,width,height)
                     _spriteBatch.End()



If you want to add sprites 
- Write ->  Sprite sprite; // sprite is a variable name
- Write in LoadContent() -> texture= Content.Load<Texture2D>("name");
                            sprite = new Sprite(texture, Vector2.Zero); // if you add another sprite change the Sprite to Player or another class
- Write in Draw() -> _sp.Begin()
                     _sp.Draw(sprite.texture,sprite.position, Color.White) //texture and position is in sprite class
                     _sp.End()

- Add new class -> public Player : Sprite  
//look at the player class the rest of them writing in there.